gy/</guid></item><item><title>特朗普已年满 80 岁，现任世界领导人中最年长和最年轻的是谁？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/09/as-trump-turns-80-who-are-the-oldest-and-youngest-current-world-leaders/</link><description>随着特朗普年满 80 岁，186 名国家领导人中只有 16 人年龄更大。领导人年龄中位数为 63 岁，尼泊尔总理 36 岁，是最年轻的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 02:08:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/09/as-trump-turns-80-who-are-the-oldest-and-youngest-current-world-leaders/</guid></item><item><title>以色列人、巴勒斯坦人、美国人对伊朗战争有不同看法</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/09/israelis-palestinians-americans-see-war-in-iran-differently/</link><description>四分之三的以色列人认为美国在攻击伊朗方面做出了正确的决定，而十分之八的巴勒斯坦人则持相反观点。美国人的分歧更大。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:24:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/09/israelis-palestinians-americans-see-war-in-iran-differently/</guid></item><item><title>大约五分之一的美国人使用过加密货币；共和党人的使用有所增加</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/08/about-1-in-5-americans-have-used-crypto-republicans-use-has-ticked-up/</link><description>加密货币使用中最大的人口差异是性别、年龄和收入。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 01:56:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/08/about-1-in-5-americans-have-used-crypto-republicans-use-has-ticked-up/</guid></item><item><title>万斯是 1.5% 的美国人中皈依天主教的人之一</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/vance-is-among-1-5-of-americans-who-have-converted-to-catholicism/</link><description>美国天主教徒中皈依者占 8%。剩下的 92% 的美国天主教徒是在这种信仰中长大的，并且至今仍然认同这种信仰。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 01:59:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/vance-is-among-1-5-of-americans-who-have-converted-to-catholicism/</guid></item><item><title>美国人表示，跟上关键新闻话题至关重要。但很少有人说他们自己消息灵通</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/americans-say-keeping-up-with-key-news-topics-is-crucial-but-fewer-say-theyre-highly-informed-themselves/</link><description>民主党人和共和党人在评估了解各种话题的重要性方面大体表现出相似的模式。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 01:44:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/americans-say-keeping-up-with-key-news-topics-is-crucial-but-fewer-say-theyre-highly-informed-themselves/</guid></item><item><title>36个国家的大多数人对以色列持负面看法，对内塔尼亚胡缺乏信心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/04/most-people-across-36-countries-have-negative-views-of-israel-and-little-confidence-in-netanyahu/</link><description>在我们调查的大多数国家中，大多数人都对以色列持负面看法，对总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡 (Benjamin Netanyahu) 缺乏信心或没有信心。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 02:08:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/04/most-people-across-36-countries-have-negative-views-of-israel-and-little-confidence-in-netanyahu/</guid></item></channel></rss>